# CPU Scheduling Simulator — SJF & Priority

A Java Swing desktop application that simulates and compares four CPU scheduling algorithms side-by-side, complete with Gantt charts, performance metrics, and starvation detection.

---

## 📋 Overview

This project implements and visually compares:

| Algorithm | Type |
|---|---|
| **SJF** — Shortest Job First | Non-Preemptive |
| **SRTF** — Shortest Remaining Time First | Preemptive |
| **Priority Scheduling** | Non-Preemptive |
| **Preemptive Priority Scheduling** | Preemptive |

The simulator runs all four algorithms simultaneously on the same input, allowing direct performance comparison through Gantt charts, results tables, ready queue logs, and a conclusion report.

---

## Features

- **Interactive GUI** — Add processes manually or load built-in test scenarios
- **4 Gantt Charts** — Visual timeline of execution order and preemption points for each algorithm
- **Metrics Tables** — Per-process CT, TAT, WT, and RT for all four algorithms
- **Ready Queue Log** — Tracks how processes enter and leave the ready queue over time
- **Conclusion Report** — Automatic comparative analysis with starvation detection and best-algorithm recommendation
- **Input Validation** — Rejects negative arrival times, zero burst times, non-numeric input, and duplicate PIDs
- **Preset Scenarios** — 4 built-in scenarios covering basic workloads, BT vs Priority conflict, starvation risk, and validation edge cases

---

##  How to Run

### Requirements
- Java JDK 8 or higher
- NetBeans IDE (recommended) **or** any Java IDE / command line

### Run via NetBeans
1. Open NetBeans and select **File → Open Project**
2. Navigate to the `OSproject` folder and open it
3. Click **Run Project** (F6)

### Run via Command Line
```bash
# Navigate to the project directory
cd OSproject

# Compile all source files
javac -d build/classes src/model/*.java src/metrics/*.java src/scheduler/*.java src/gui/*.java

# Run the application
java -cp build/classes gui.MainGUI
```

---

## 🖥️ How to Use

1. **Add Processes** — Enter PID, Arrival Time (AT), Burst Time (BT), and Priority, then click **Add Process**
2. **Load a Scenario** — Click any of the scenario buttons (A, B, C, D) to auto-fill a preset test case
3. **Run Simulation** — Click **Run Simulation** to execute all four algorithms simultaneously
4. **View Results** — Scroll through the Gantt charts, metrics tables, ready queue log, and conclusion
5. **Clear / Reset** — Use the Clear or Reset buttons to start over

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
OSproject/
├── src/
│   ├── gui/
│   │   ├── MainGUI.java          # Main application window (Swing)
│   │   └── GanttChartPanel.java  # Custom Gantt chart rendering
│   ├── model/
│   │   ├── Process.java          # Process data model
│   │   └── GanttData.java        # Gantt chart data model
│   ├── scheduler/
│   │   ├── SJFScheduler.java              # SJF Non-Preemptive
│   │   ├── SRTFScheduler.java             # SRTF Preemptive
│   │   ├── PriorityScheduler.java         # Priority Non-Preemptive
│   │   └── PreemptivePriorityScheduler.java # Priority Preemptive
│   └── metrics/
│       └── MetricsCalculator.java         # CT, TAT, WT, RT calculations
└── nbproject/                    # NetBeans project config
```

---

## 📊 Metrics Explained

| Metric | Formula | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **CT** — Completion Time | — | Time when process finishes execution |
| **TAT** — Turnaround Time | CT − AT | Total time from arrival to completion |
| **WT** — Waiting Time | TAT − BT | Time spent waiting in the ready queue |
| **RT** — Response Time | Start Time − AT | Time from arrival to first CPU assignment |

---

## ⚖️ Algorithm Trade-offs

- **SJF / SRTF** optimize for minimum average waiting time — best for throughput-focused systems
- **Priority / Preemptive Priority** ensure critical processes run first — essential for real-time systems
- **Preemptive algorithms** respond faster but introduce context-switching overhead
- **Priority algorithms** risk **starvation** for low-priority processes unless an aging mechanism is added

